title: This Week’s Gridiron Matchups
text:
High school football games involving schools from Barbour County: 
All Games kickoff at 7 p.m. 
FRIDAY, Oct. 16 
WHO: Greenville Tigers at Eufaula Tigers 
WHERE: at Tiger Stadium, Eufaula 
SERIES: Eufaula leads, 15-9 
LAST MEETING: 2014, Greenville 30, Eufaula 0 
Records: Greenville (7-0, 4-0); Eufaula (6-1, 4-0) 
COACHES: Josh McLendon (7-0 in first season at Greenville); Bryan Moore (6-1 in first season at Eufaula) 
Noteworthy: Eufaula won seven straight in the series from 1999-2007, but the two teams did not meet again until last year’s shutout by Greenville. Of the 24 career meetings, seven were in the state playoffs with Greenville winning five of those. Eufaula did win the 1999 first-round meeting, 40-0. 
WHO: Lakeside School Chiefs at Macon-East Academy Knights 
WHERE: at Knight Field, Cecil 
SERIES: Macon-East leads, 2-1 
LAST MEETING: 2014, Lakeside 42, Macon-East 33 
RECORDS: Lakeside School (4-3, 3-1); Macon-East (2-5, 2-3) 
COACHES: Keith Jones (4-3 in first season at Lakeside); Glynn Lott (126-90 in 20th season at Macon-East) 
Noteworthy: Glynn Lott is the only coach Macon-East Academy has ever had, dating back to the school’s first season in 1996. The teams have only met twice on the gridiron, with Macon-East winning the first two in 1996 and ’97 by large margins, and Lakeside winning last year’s shootout at Reeves Field. 
WHO: Barbour County Jaguars at Wicksburg Panthers 
WHERE: at Panther Stadium, Wicksburg 
SERIES: Barbour County leads, 2-1 
LAST MEETING: 2014, Wicksburg 52,, Barbour County 14 
RECORDS: Barbour County (0-8, 0-4); Brantley (5-3, 2-3) 
COACHES: Chris Reynolds (0-18 in second season at Barbour County); Josh Cox (9-9 in second season at Wicksburg) 
Noteworthy: Barbour County won the first two meetings between these schools – 2010 by seven and 2011 by one – before losing big last year. The Panthers became the first team to score all season on Pike County last week, although it was in a 47-8 loss to the Bulldogs.
